'''''Star Wars Insider'' 47''' is the forty-seventh issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in [[January]] [[2000]]. Issue 47 featured the first "flesh and blood" image of [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] character [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]], as portrayed by model [[Shannon McRandle]] for [[Decipher]]'s [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|''Star Wars'' Customizable Card Game]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"From the Editor's Desk"
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[Star News]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|''In the'' Star Wars ''Universe'']]: [[Mike Quinn]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*"[[The Horse's Mouth|Straight from the Horse's Mouth]]" &ndash; Wedding Bells and Wookiee Yells {{C|by [[Peet Janes]]}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &ndash; There's Gold in Them Thar Cans {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[Prequel Profile]]: [[Ty Teiger]]" {{C|by [[Jamie Painter]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Last Page]]"

===Features===
*"[[Natalie Portman & Pernilla August: Women of the Force]]" {{C|by [[Kevin Fitzpatrick]]}}
*:<small>The women in [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Anakin Skywalker's]] life reflect on the events of [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|Episode I]] and use the Force to see a glimpse of [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|Episode II]]. The ''Insider''{{'s}} [[Kevin Fitzpatrick]] chronicles the words of the Queen and Mother of the ''Star Wars'' universe.</small>
*"[[Peter Mayhew: Chewie Lives!]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>The man inside the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] talks for the first time about Chewie's "death" in the novel ''[[Vector Prime]]'', as well as the character's new comic book, classic trilogy memories, and his powerful night at the MTV Movie Awards. Plus, [[Del Rey]] Books explains its controversial decision. Lifelong Chewie fanatic [[Scott Chernoff]] does it all for the Wookiee.</small>
*"[[Mara Jade: Flesh and Blood]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>Finally, an all-out look at the most popular character in the ''Star Wars'' Expanded Universe! Scott Chernoff goes behind the scenes at the photo shoot for Mara Jade's new Decipher card—the first "life-action" rendering of the new Mrs. Skywalker—and talks to character creator [[Timothy Zahn]] about the evolution and future of the former [[Emperor's Hand/Legends|Emperor's Hand]]. It's a Mara Jade blow-out!</small>
*"[[Creatures of Episode I]]" {{C|by [[Terryl Whitlatch]]}}
*:<small>From the waters of [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]] to the sands of [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] a new menagerie of memorable creatures is unleashed in the first episode of the ''Star Wars'' saga. [[Daniel Wallace]], author of the upcoming [[The Essential Guide to Episode I|''Essential Guide to Episode I'']], chats with artist [[Terryl Whitlatch]] about creature creation in this fantastic photo-filled feature.</small>
*"[[Star Wars Rocks II: Jedi Boogaloo|''Star Wars'' Rocks II: Jedi Boogaloo]]" {{C|by [[Jon Bradley Snyder]]}}
*:<small>[[Jon Bradley Snyder]] returns to the record store for another look at the sometimes bizarre, sometimes hilarious, always rocking music inspired by the ''Star Wars'' saga. Rock, rap, metal, lounge, calypso—it's all here, along with another brand new ''Star Wars'' Rocks painting by the ''Insider''{{'s}} [[Hugh Fleming]]. For those about to rock, we salute you!</small>

